assuming she is naked...<br>
<br>
The thing about GiTS though, is that it's a non-sexual context. True, she's naked not nude (art term...nude would be like a faerie or something that doesn't have clothes in the first place), but there is a, um, lack of detail. Still, you have to back up and consider *why* you find it offensive. For the most part, taboos on nudity are cultural. Like nsdf rand said, Americans are more desensitized to violence than nudity. I've lived in several countries (including Japan), so I can vouch for the truth in that. Other countries don't think of it as such a big deal.<br>
<br>
If you want to see decayed morals, American TV and movies show that to you more than anime does, and certainly more that GiTS. Leaving hentai out of the picture, since there's certainly a large porn industry in the U.S. too. Many R rated movies show sex and/or nudity, and even some PG-13 ones (Titanic anyone?). GiTS is rated R. Put it in that context, and it's actually rather tame for the rating. What's odd perhaps is that it's a &quot;cartoon&quot;. A drawing...well...don't go anywhere near an art museum is all I have to say. You wanna see sick, perverted minds, look at artists (and I mean that in the best possible way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). <br>
The more of art, anime, movies, and such that I see...the less I think the statue type nudity in GiTS is anything to think twice about.  Needed though? No, of course not. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=durakken>Durakken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/18/03 9:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ghost in the shell, why so much nudity!?</span><hr size=1> ok i'm not saying this is why there is nudity in GiTS, but scientifically the reason that she is naked when she uses her stealth crap is that it creates less flicker and is less complicated. The only way this technology would work is if you absorb the visable light on one side and then project it on the other side...now if you had clothing do this you would have to have sensors which would pick up ever fold that could possably be and there for would be less likely to be able to maintain much invisability. if you have a pretty much stationary mass that you are working with that can only move in a limited range of motion it is much easier and much more effective. although no matter what it would all be pointless less you move pretty slow because the motion would create a shimmer or a deluded image upon the surface and also it may blur due to light hitting it at certain times. But her cloaking with either skin tight suit or nude is just more effective. In all the scenes in the movie the nudity was used in this way and is there fore well done and you should have no problem with it. The only other nudity is her being created and that is also accurately put in because nothing like that is made with clothes on.<br>
